{
  "texts": [
    "The course ran continuously, once or twice a year, from 1976 to 1998.",
    "From the start, all federal judges were invited to apply, yet Henry Manne did not have any existing relationships with federal judges.",
    "The LEC made the program attractive by covering all expenses for a beachside hotel stay, and by inviting judges' family members to join.",
    "The organizers did not invite particular judges, and the admissions process was rst-come-rst-serve. 9",
    "This means, importantly, that there was no selection of particular judges for attendance on the side of the program organizers."
  ]
}